title: Watch Relativity attempt the first launch of its 3D-printed rocket Terran 1
summary: 3D-printing specialist Relativity Space is attempting its first rocket launch on Saturday, a mission that marks the most significant test yet of the company’s ambitious manufacturing approach.

title: Watch live: Relativity Space preps 3D-printed rocket for second launch attempt
summary: Relativity Space will try again Saturday to launch its 3D-printed Terran 1 rocket into orbit from Cape Canaveral after halting a countdown earlier in the week to ensure propellants loaded into the launcher were at the proper temperature. The three-hour launch window opens at 1 p.m. EST (1800 GMT).

title: SpaceX capsule with four-person crew departs space station, heads for Earth
summary: Closing out five months on the International Space Station, two NASA astronauts, a five-time Japanese space flier, and a Russian cosmonaut departed the complex Saturday inside a SpaceX Dragon crew capsule, heading for a parachute-assisted splashdown in the Gulf of Mexico around 19 hours later.

title: Meet The Startup Developing The Next Generation of Satellite Technology
summary: As the commercial space industry shifts into rapidly reusable launch vehicles, the satellite industry has been lagging behind with slow and costly development. K2 Space wants to shock the industry and develop platforms to fully utilize the new age of spaceflight, with Starship and Falcon 9 being major targets for K2’s satellite buses.

title: Crew Dragon Endurance returning to Earth on Crew-5 mission
summary: The Crew-5 astronauts are returning to Earth on the evening of Saturday, March 11, after spending the last five months aboard the International Space Station. Nicole Mann and Josh Cassada of NASA, Koichi Wakata of JAXA, and Anna Kikina of Roscosmos are preparing to undock their Crew Dragon, C210 Endurance, early on Saturday at 2:20 AM EST (07:20 UTC).
